cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about a convolutional neural network for optical flow estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents novel approaches to improve flow estimation accuracy and regularization, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of feature warping, which could relate to robotics (cs.RO) or multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
